actions.comment:
Thanks for reporting this. You're correct — `SKCanvas.DrawSurface` and `SKSurface.Draw` don't accept `SKSamplingOptions`, and the legacy `FilterQuality` path isn't wired through for surface drawing (unlike `DrawImage` which was updated).

Here's a workaround you can use while we work on the proper fix: take a snapshot of the surface and use `DrawImage` which already supports sampling options:

```csharp
using var image = surface.Snapshot();
var sampling = new SKSamplingOptions(SKFilterMode.Linear, SKMipmapMode.Linear);
canvas.DrawImage(image, x, y, sampling, paint);
```

The upstream Skia C++ API does support a sampling parameter on `SkSurface::draw` — it just wasn't exposed through our C shim and C# bindings. PR #3491 adds the missing overloads.
